</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,1324,2034]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1756,1782]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Remarks</emphasis>
. The single specimen available is in a poor condition being somewhat squashed, thus preventing illustrations at the same level as the remaining species herein. There are however enough characters to allow newly collected specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lilljeborg" authorityYear="1865" box="[413,473,1829,1854]" class="Malacostraca" family="Synopiidae" genus="Tiron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[413,473,1829,1854]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Tiron</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to be recognised as belonging to this new species, especially if found on the southeast coast of 
<collectingCountry box="[246,310,1864,1890]" name="Japan" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Japan</collectingCountry>
centering around the Sagami Sea. In this connection it is of interest to draw attention to an excellent colour photo of a specimen listed as 
<taxonomicName box="[573,674,1900,1926]" class="Malacostraca" family="Synopiidae" genus="Tiron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[573,633,1901,1926]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Tiron</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
(JAMBIO, see reference). It was collected 
<date box="[1174,1376,1900,1926]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="2014-02-19">19 February 2014</date>
(100 years after Th. Mortensen’s efforts) in the eastern Sagami Bay at 35˚08’N 139˚34.6’E off Miura. Based on the shape of the cephalon and the structure of the urosome it may be a specimen of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Just" authorityYear="2022" box="[973,1171,1973,1998]" class="Malacostraca" family="Synopiidae" genus="Tiron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sagamiense">
<emphasis box="[973,1171,1973,1998]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Tiron sagamiense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
described above.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
